description: With Thomas in a rush to get a ton of hay bales delivered to the mainland by the end of the day, he tasks Terence the Tractor and Carly to assemble all the bales in his stead. Carly and Terence manage to get everything together quickly, but soon Terence purposefully crashes into the hay bales sending loose hay all over the place! Carly is shocked and confused, and Terence explains that he can bale the hay again with his trusty baler in no time. They turn the hay-bale stacking into a game, forming all kinds of structures Terence can crash into, until they finally form the tallest hay tower ever. When Thomas finally arrives to pick up the hay, he's worried they won't have enough time to complete the delivery, but Terence reminds him that they can work and have fun all at the same time.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: The First Day
description: Best friends Oscar and Hedgehog get dropped off at their first day at summer camp.

title: Blackout!
description: When a storm knocks out power for the whole island, Thomas volunteers to deliver a generator from Kellsthorpe to Knapford. He's determined to complete this task on his own and initially refuses all offers of help, but he soon becomes overwhelmed with complications. Sandy and Carly show up to teach Thomas that everyone needs a little help sometimes, and the three watch as all the engines on Sodor team up to complete the delivery.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Malgax Attacks
description: Ben finally manages to rid himself of Skurd... just when he needs the Slime-Biot most.

title: Oscar and the Monsters Chapter 1: Unaccompanied Oscar
description: When Oscar isn't invited to Alexa's birthday party, Mortimer tries to make him feel better by telling him about a similar time in his life. Ever the glowworm, Oscar sneaks back in time to help a young Mortimer overcome the sad experience.

title: The Emily Ghost Institute for Manners and Magical Etiquette
description: Oscar and Hedgehog go to a magical etiquette class.

title: Yelloween/Lunch Ahoy
description: It's Yelloween! Stellar tries to protect Piper from being scared -- but a mysterious pineapple-gobbling goblin suddenly appears! When Stellar brings her own lunch to Pirate Diner and it goes missing, the kids become pirates to find the lost "treasure."

title: Apple's in Trouble
description: Apple is challenged to a fight by a grumpy Cheesesteak, so he and Onion go on a quest to find the source of Cheesesteak's grumpiness.

title: Elements Part 1: Skyhooks
description: Upon returning to Ooo, Finn and Jake discover that there have been some radical changes in their absence.

title: Susie and Ramona Chapter 1: Susie's Ark
description: When Susie learns magic is beginning to disappear from New York, she tries to lead all the magical creatures to safety.

title: Ben 10,000 Returns
description: Eon is back and it's up to an older and wiser Ben from the future to help the crew defeat him using the Hands of Armageddon to win the battle.

title: The Filth
description: Ben is tasked with cleaning the Rust Bucket. But when he is tricked into letting the villainous and vile Fly Guys steal it, he must chase them down before they create an unstoppable maggot monster with sights firmly set on destroying Las Vegas.

title: Rath of Con
description: Back stateside, Ben can't get into a cat cosplay competition, Top Tail, without a costume of his own; but when he goes Rath, a new cat-like alien with an attitude, Ben's newfound wild side quickly becomes much more than he bargained for.

title: Ben 10 Returns Part 1
description: Ben Tennyson is a normal teenager who has put away his toys including the Omnitrix that gave him his powers. Ben's life take a turn when he is attacked by an alien and discovers Grandpa Max is missing. To find his grandpa, Ben teams up with his cousin, Gwen, his grandpa's partner, Magister, and even his former nemesis, Kevin 11. When they discover the Forever Knights (a secret organization that deals in illegal alien technology) and DNAliens (the Highbreeds henchmen) are trading dangerous weapons, Ben decides to once again put on the Omnitrix and quickly learns he can now transform into ten new aliens.

title: Rumble Brothers/The Blame Game
description: Twins Josh and Jamie are usually together, but they seek their own space after a big argument ... until a storm breaks out! Stellar proves her innocence by playing detectives with Josh ... and pinning the blame on Piper.

title: Pepper and the Fog
description: After the island gets covered in fog, Pepper attempts to make it to Susie's house.

title: It Was Them
description: Dr. Animo has escaped his Plumber prison, and Ben and Rook must track him down before he turns the world into his personal mutant ant farm! (Introducing Nemetrix alien Slamworm, Galvan Plumbers Blukic and Driba, Arctiguana, new Ben alien Crashhopper.)

title: Mud Is Thicker Than Water
description: Ben, Gwen and Cousin Lucy try to find out how Psyphon's thugs are getting Plumber technology.

title: If All Else Fails
description: A hibernating Highbreed officer awakens and triggers a device designed to destroy the planet. Now Ben must figure out a way to stop him.

title: Not So Easy-Greasy
description: Nia is nervous about working with Tess, the fastest -- and bossiest -- crane on Sodor! When Nia's plan for a safe and speedy delivery goes awry and causes Tess' wheels to clog with sand, they recruit handy Sandy to solve their problem. Luckily, Sandy has a new invention to get Tess up and going again: a tanker full of her Super-Slick Easy-Greasy Crane Grease! However, chaos continues to ensue when Nia gets stuck in the mud and the runaway grease spills all over Sodor! In the midst of the madness, Nia learns how to fix her original plan and save Sodor from slipping and sliding!
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Birds of a Feather
description: Ben and company help the prince of the arachna-chimps, Simian, return to power.

title: Bright Lights, Black Hearts
description: Ben, Gwen, and Max stop by the graveyard set of Gwen's favorite TV show, The Unalivers, but when Ben discovers its lead, Michael Morningstar, is an energy vampire he goes alien to show the world the real star of the show: Heatblast.

title: Wheels of Fortune
description: Team Tennyson's thrift store shopping is ruined by the latest high-speed heist of LaGrange — who is now aided by a super-fast electromagnetic racing car — and Ben must convince Kevin 11 to help stop the speed demon's globetrotting robbing spree.

title: Voided
description: Ben goes into the Null Void to aid the Plumber's Helpers defeat D'Void.

title: The Fastest Fast Food Fiend!
description: When Scooby and Shaggy compete in a fast food eating competition sponsored by the Doc Tally restaurant chain, they meet their ultimate challenge eating against none other than comedian Jim Gaffigan! And there's a horrible monster trying to stop the whole contest from finishing. Can Shaggy, Scooby and our mystery solving gang team up with Jim Gaffigan to save the fast food competition, and themselves?

title: For a Few Brains More
description: Ben, Rook and Max must stop Ultimate Albedo from absorbing Azmuth's intelligence and taking over the galaxy.

title: Betsy and Ghost Chapter 3: There's A Racket In My Hope Chest
description: The witches search for Betsy - who doesn't want to be found. Can she learn to love being a witch as much as she loves being a ghost?

title: River of Gold
description: Apple and Onion find a mysterious book but they better read it fast before it disappears forever.

title: Duped
description: Under pressure from his newfound fame, Ben comes up with a plan to be at more than one place at a time.

title: Perplexahedron
description: Ben, Kevin and Gwen race Aggregor through a mysterious artificial planetoid designed to destroy anyone who enters.

title: Prey or Play
description: After receiving a super-exclusive ticket to Adrenaland, Ben leaves behind Grandpa Max and Gwen to enjoy the perks of being the parks only attendant, but when he learns he's not alone, our hero must now contend with the only kid who could afford the price of admission: Billy Billions!

title: Susie and Ramona Chapter 2: Ghost Baby Jabberwock
description: Susie, Ramona, and Barb team up in frozen time to see what's threatening magic.

title: The Prince and the Birthday Bluesies
description: When Prince Ivandoe gets a case of the "Birthday Bluesies", Bert is determined to throw him a Stag Kingdom party with all of his favorite treats. Meanwhile an increasingly "sophisticated" Ivandoe becomes curious to discover the grown-up world.
originalseriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe

title: Glow Worm
description: While Hedgehog is off "werewolfing," a deflated Oscar has a therapy session with Shark that helps him realize the magic within him.

title: Ye Olde Laser Duel
description: As team Tennyson admires the efficiency of a super modern train station, Ben is quick to sniff out one of Steam Smythe's robots holding up the line. Once the fed up villain tricks our hero into accepting a duel, the fate of the Omnitrix hangs in the balance and it's up to Ben to set things right.

title: The Purge
description: The Forever Knights factions have been united into one and an all-out war against the aliens on Earth erupts.

title: The 11th Alien
description: Ben must overcome his doubts and fully embrace his new powers if he is to beat Vilgax and the Weatherheads.

title: Windy Day/ Hand Me Downs/ Me and My Shadow
description: Sonia, Hugo and Mel have Sunday adventures with paper boats, sharing hand me downs, and learning there are more ways than one to play.

title: Popular Banana Split
description: Hedgehog and Max discover a tiny high school when they are accidentally shrunk by a science experiment.

title: Hide and Surprise!
description: While playing hide and seek with Percy, Diesel accidentally gets stranded on a barge that floats out to sea, where it becomes a group effort to rescue him.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Got to Go/Bye-Bye Octi/Family Photo
description: Sonia, Hugo and Mel have Sunday adventures getting ready for a party, making friends with an octopus, and taking pictures around the patio.

title: The Case of the Missing Crane
description: When Carly does not return from saving Emily from an accidental derailing, a worried Sandy recruits the help of a bored Diesel to find her best gal pal. The unlikely pair become detectives, traveling throughout the island in search of clues. Will they be able to solve the mystery of the missing crane?
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Merry Christmas
description: When the Rustbucket's A/C goes on the fritz in the middle of the desert, Ben, Max and Gwen take refuge at Holiday Village, an over the top Christmas theme park that seems to appear out of nowhere. The place is run by an evil entity known as Mr. Jingles, who takes Max prisoner because he believes Max is Santa! It's up to Ben and Gwen to free Max and break the spell Mr. Jingles has cast on Holiday Village, freeing others who've been trapped their for years and releasing the theme park.

title: A Pastime for Petunia/Looney Tunes Zoo (song)/Pouting Match
description: A Pastime for Petunia: Petunia has a difficult time finding a hobby that doesn't imitate the other babies' interests./Pouting Match: Lola tries pouting to get what she wants, and soon all the babies are doing it.

title: The Babies Chapter 2: Teacup Giant
description: Susie sends Alexa to the Fjords to train as a giant, but her small size causes her to lag behind. Will Alexa be able to fake it until she makes it - or are these boots too enormous to fill?

title: Double Daddies Day/The Pickle Fixer
description: Apple double-duty organizes Father's Day for her two Dads. Will she crush it or face a Double Daddies Day Disaster? On Dad's first day as a stay-at-home parent, Stellar plays teacher to show him parenting is a breeze!

title: Scary Tara/Home School Day/New Library Book
description: Lu meets big Tara, helps Dad with work, and searches the library for a new book.

title: Tub on the Run
description: While Hedgehog and Max scour the island in search of a missing tub, everyone is dying to know: are things weird between them?

title: Long Long Line/The Chalk/Elodie Wants to Decide
description: Biba waits in line, the bugs get some new chalk, and Lu meets Elodie's cousin.

title: Franken-Fight
description: Ben hops into the Rustbuggy for a driving lesson along the sand dunes of Cape Cod, but he takes a freaky switchback turn when the Rustbuggy is mutated into a motor-monster by Bootleg, another alien transformation of Kevin 11, with powers similar to Upgrade!

title: Ken 10
description: We're back in the future with Ben 10K, and this time he has a son, Ken. On Ken's tenth birthday, Ben gives him his very own Omnitrix. Ben must come to learn to trust Ken with the power of the Omnitrix. Along the way, Ken befriends a kid named Devlin. Devlin turns out to be Kevin 11's son and was merely using Ken so he could break his dad out of the Null Void. Ben 10K and Ken then team up to take down Kevin 11. As for Devlin, he comes to realize his dad is a jerk, and realizes the error of his ways. He's able to redeem himself, proving he's a good kid and joining forces with "Team Tennyson."

title: A New Dawn
description: The Time War brings Ben, Rook, and George Washington together to battle an alien conqueror.

title: The Song of Mystery
description: A hideous creature named Que Horrifico is turning the children of Crystal Cove in to monsters. The adults in the town are in shock, reacting in the only way they know how, by abandoning their children and running away like cowards. Only Scooby and the gang stay behind to solve the mystery. Going undercover as a family - "Dad" Fred, "Mom" Daphne, "Grandma" Velma, "Son" Shaggy and "Baby" Scooby - the gang rents a house in order to capture Que Horrifico. But when their plan backfires and Que Horrifico uses his power over the monster children to cause them to attack the gang, it looks like all is lost. That is until a cartoon character named Broccoli Head comes to their rescue.

title: Mission: Stuffed Animal
description: When Redbird takes one of Buff's stuffed animals without asking and it accidentally gets swiped by the Legion of Zoom, Red enlists Bam to help him make a daring rescue.

title: Win It or Bin It
description: Apple and Onion are about to take ownership of a brand new luxury penthouse apartment and be rid of their roof shack for ever! All they need is a good reference from a previous landlord… Falafel.

title: Officer Moody
description: Pieces of Mr. Reese's past are revealed when his old partner on the police force, Officer Moody, visits Aberdale Elementary.

title: Fruit Caboose/ Bin Bug/ Bug Hugs
description: The bugs learn about sharing, Lu hogs the funnest role in a game, and Barnaby learns about sharing hugs.

title: The Beast Inside
description: Ben, Gwen and Max make a return to Max's alma mater but this time it's no homecoming. Dr. Animo has made a scary transformation and found a way to release the very dangerous animal nature of humans, including Max's life-long friend!

title: The Enemy of My Frenemy
description: Gwen hopes to rescue Charmcaster. When she asks Hex to join her, he refuses saying he won't join a suicide mission.

title: Keep It Fresh
description: It's Apple's turn to buy this months' groceries again meaning that the risk of starvation is at hand.

title: Topsy Turvy Table/Smelly Sticker Games
description: Stellar plans a fancy lunch for Mom at Cafe Fancy Schmancy, but playful pirates make it an un-fancy adventure! The Dads help Apple complete her chore chart by turning it into a game: The Smelly Sticker Chore Challenge!

title: Nightbike
description: Bibi has some competition with Nightwing's motorcycle, Nightbike. Always trying to one-up each other, these stunt bikes will need to learn that they're better when they work together.

title: The Final Countdown
description: Rook and his little Plumbers must defend the Base from a mysterious lockdown.

title: Riding the Storm Out
description: Ben and Gwen's camping trip is interrupted by the emotionless Weatherheads (Gust-o, Hail-o, & Shock-o) but a malfunctioning Omnitrix firing out a mishmash of aliens may not be the forecast for success.

title: Etiquette Clarence
description: Clarence submits a short story into a creative writing contest, and he's overjoyed when he learns he's accepted as a finalist! But when Jeff finds out Clarence has to attend a formal dinner, he fixates on transforming the messy Clarence into a proper gentleman.

title: Susie and her Sister Chapter 2: Hot Corn Girls
description: On her 15th birthday, Susie must prepare for her Gibbous Rite Ceremony. Will Mildred be able to keep her chaotic magic in check for just one day so Susie can become the full witch woman of her dreams?

title: The Fast and The Furriest/A Tale of Two Forts
description: Apple realizes it's her own fault that she's always late to school! With Papa, they race the clock to get to school on time. Apple and Josh's creative differences split them up to build two forts -- a princess castle and a rocket ship.

title: New Mail Engine in Town
description: After Percy gets in an accident and ends up with a broken axle, Nia temporarily takes over his mail delivery duties for him - and her mail delivery is even quicker! Percy thinks the replacement is permanent. In an attempt to find his new thing, Percy tries out different jobs all over Sodor, but nothing seems to fit him quite right. When he's just about ready to give up and head to the mainland, everyone agrees quick is not better. They all miss Percy's caring, careful way of delivering the mail. He's the best engine for the job!
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Ben 4 Good Buddy
description: Out on a desert highway, a group of modern day highway pirates hijack the Rustbucket, trick it out and use it in a daring robbery. And while Ben and Gwen are at first glad to get rid of that "bucket of bolts", they come to realize the Rustbucket is "a part of the family." In the end our trio heroes get Max's beloved "ride" back and bring down these pirates once and for all.

title: Babies on the Block/Beach Bath/The Biggest Joy
description: Sonia, Hugo and Mel have Sunday adventures playing with their baby friends, building a bath at the beach, and remembering joyful family moments.

title: Max's Monster
description: Grandpa Max's old Plumber partner, Phil, seeks Max's help to tame the monster within. (Introducing new Ben alien, Buzzshock; Re-introducing old Ben alien, Benvicktor.)

title: Dog King Clarence
description: When Clarence's neighbor Gale recruits him to dog sit for her, he knows it will be a breeze, being the self-proclaimed "Dog King," Clarence knows all there is to know about pups. Nevertheless, Gale's dog proves to be a little more challenging than he expects!

title: Positive Attitude Theory
description: Apple and Onion spend a day in Falafel's shoes and use their positive attitude to prove he shouldn't be so grumpy.

title: Billy Bajillions
description: In Aspen, Colorado, Ben, Gwen, and Grandpa Max are on a hike to find the Forgeti, but when they realize they've stumbled upon Billy Billions own "Winter in July" ski resort, Ben must battle Billy, with an assist from the Forgeti itself.

title: I Can Catch/That's My Favourite/Tidy Up
description: Lu learns to accept help, Declan learns to share a favorite thing, and Biba learns that accidents happen.

title: In Charm's Way
description: Kevin is charmed by a beautiful girl and finds himself under her spell (literally) as Charmcaster has returned and is forcing Kevin to do her biding.

title: The Prince and the Feather Fluffer-Upper
description: Prince Ivandoe and Bert reluctantly agree to bring Princess Syllabob of the Underwater Kingdom an all-powerful Trident for her Sweet Sixteenth birthday. However, it is currently in the possession of Ivandoe's great nemesis - Prince Svan - who has found another, less dignified, use for it. Ivandoe and Bert must risk all, entering the Swan Palace and avoiding the appalling Royal Family, in order to fulfill their promise to King Axalotyl, King of the Deep.
originalseriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe

title: Fear the Fogg
description: As Max attempts to get Ben and Gwen to the Four Corners Monument before sunset, an ominous fog bank engulfs the roadway and forces Max to drive at a snails pace, but once The Fogg comes to life and attacks the Rust Bucket, Team Tennyson must work together if they are to navigate to safety.

title: The Yolk's on You/Baby Elmer Had a Friend (song)/Baby-Gate
description: The Yolk's on You: Daffy and Melissa team up to play jokes on the other babies./Baby Gate: Melissa spreads rumors about the babies, and Bugs goes undercover to find the truth.

title: Chocolate Money Badgers
description: Oscar learns that he can earn merit badges that unlock prizes.

title: Carly's Magnificent Magnet
description: When Carly gets a new magnet to help Tess the Troublesome Crane load up a shipment of metal crates, she struggles with the new tool. Carly is frustrated that she's making mistakes during the job. Sandy and Thomas reassure Carly that she needs give herself time to be bad at it. Mistakes are part of learning something new! When Sandy ends up careening towards the water, Carly will have to put her new knowledge to the test and hope she won't make another mistake.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: What Rhymes with Omnitrix?
description: At a poetry slam event, Charmcaster's reading of Kevin's poetry causes magical trouble for Ben and Gwen, causing mind swaps that have everyone confused as to who's fighting who.

title: Bruno's Map Mishap
description: Bruno is beyond delighted -- he has received the gift of an updated map of Sodor from Sir Topham Hatt! He and Thomas can't wait to use it to navigate their busy schedule for the day. But when Kana's speedy whoosh blows Bruno's beloved map up, up, and away, Thomas and Bruno team up with Percy and Diesel to recover it! While searching the island far and wide for Bruno's prized possession, the gang discovers that there is something more important than keeping their schedules -- their friendship!
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Super-Villain Team-Up
description: After a lull in alien antics, a restless Ben suggests to Max and Gwen that he might be a better hero if he went solo, but once Vilgax enlists the help of Zombozo to build a giant hypno-mechanism to hypnotize the entire world, Ben must rethink his strategy if he is to defeat the super-villain team-up.

title: Seeking a Safer Sodor
description: After a near-collision rattles their wheels, Percy and Kana enlist the help of Emily to introduce new safety measures all over Sodor. However, their anxiousness about accidents push Percy and Kana to ridiculous extremes that only makes more trouble! When Percy has another accident caused by his off-the-rails safety obsession, he refuses to leave Tidmouth Sheds. When he has to leap into action to help his friends, Percy learns that paying attention to your surroundings is the best way to not have an accident.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Mystery Boxcars
description: Kana is upset when she keeps running out of power, but a mystery scavenger hunt is just the thing to cheer her up.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Tu Ba or Not Tu Ba
description: The class tries to help Chef achieve his dream of joining the world's most famous Tuba Band, Tubalicious, only to regret it when they realize how much they'll miss him.

title: Too Far
description: When Baby Bop's playful teasing starts bothering Mel, Barney arranges a trip to the Castleverse where their adventure motivates Mel to finally speak up for herself.

title: Spin Out/Taz's Fridge (song)/Snow Day
description: Spinout: Taz learns a tough lesson. He shouldn't spin after eating too much candy./Snow Day: The babies experience their first snowfall.

title: Vengeance of Vilgax Part 1
description: Armed with the power of 10 Alien Champions, Vilgax sets his sites on Earth. And the only hero standing in his way Is Ben Tennyson.

title: Drone On
description: Ben and Gwen are in a highly competitive paper airplane war, but when alien-tech drones bombard the Rustbucket, the cousins must work together to ground the aerial attack and find out who's behind it: the alien conqueror, Vilgax!

title: Ben in Rome
description: While in Rome, Ben's quest for the best pizza helps them halt the Bugg Brother's latest culinary caper, but the vacation only gets messier when Team Tennyson stumbles upon Queen Bee's monumental heist!

title: An American Benwolf in London
description: Ben and Rook are called to London England to investigate the Forever Knights' latest activities.

title: Beach Packing/Swim Class/Wakey Wakey
description: Sonia, Hugo and Mel have Sunday adventures getting ready for the beach, learning to swim, and trying to stay awake for the fireworks.

title: Nia's Balloon Blunder
description: When a parade balloon Nia is set to deliver flies away, Thomas helps Nia adjust her plans to get it back.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Grounded
description: Ben and Gwen manage to get grounded, leaving Kevin alone to fight the DNAliens.

title: The Prince and the Kissy Curse
description: An arrogant little frogman needs the help of Prince Ivandoe to lift his curse and become the big, beautiful bullfrog he once was. Due to a technical error, Prince Ivandoe's arms have been magically replaced by slimy froggy ones. So he has no choice but to help lift the curse in order to restore his princely arms. The Frogman's hopeless attempts to find a True Love's kiss end in failure. So Ivandoe and Bert convince him that his only hope is to earn the forgiveness of The Batwitch - his ex-girlfriend - who was responsible for cursing him in the first place.
originalseriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe

title: Musical Sundays/Choices Choices/Balloon Rocket
description: Sonia, Hugo and Mel have Sunday adventures playing music, having lunch at the beach, and making a balloon experiment.

title: Of Predators and Prey Part 2
description: While trapped in Khyber's ship, Ben learns details about the origin of the Nemetrix, and the link between Khyber, Malware, and Dr. Psychobos! (Introducing new Nemetrix alien Tyrannopede.)

title: Tumble Dry Low
description: When Hedgehog's podcast blows up, she must decide whether to ride the wave of fame or stay true to her small but loyal fan base.

title: Arrested Development
description: Ben and Rook must stop the evil Robots from Dimension 12 while trapped in their own pre-pubescent bodies, thanks to Ben's childhood rival.  (Introducing Billy Billions.)

title: Summer Breakers
description: After Grandpa Max's super smart buddy Phil discovers that a second extraterrestrial item crashed alongside the Omnitrix, Team Tennyson sets off to find the second crash site before someone else does but arrive instead to find nefarious newcomer Breaker One-Nine has already beat them to the punch.

title: Drive You Crazy
description: After the Rust Bucket breaks down at a Mobile Home Park, Ben discovers they've stumbled on to the last leg of the Cali 10 Hundred, an epic, off-road auto race where mad driver Le Grange has returned for revenge against those that disqualified him years ago.

title: Honeydew Hatch
description: Oscar and Hedgehog enter Frozen Time to help Ramona grow time babies, but Ramona and Susie's broken friendship causes problems.

title: Finders Not Keepers
description: When Mel discovers the sunglasses she found belong to Grady, she still wants to keep them. Barney creates a high-seas adventure, where Mel realizes she's acting like a pirate taking what doesn't belong to her and returns the glasses.

title: DC Leader Swap
description: Robin and The Joker swap roles and lead each other's teams.

title: The Final Battle Part 1
description: Albedo Ben has stolen the Ultimatrix from Azmuth and has used it to kidnap Gwen and Kevin. So Ben goes to face Albedo Ben and rescue his friends.

title: The Dolly Vanishes/Vive Le Pew, Le Skunk (song)/Duck's Reflucks
description: The Dolly Vanishes: On an overnight train trip to visit Floyd at college, Lola's doll vanishes. Baby Bugs acts as a detective as he tries to solve the missing Edna mystery via a series of simple flashbacks, seen from each Baby Looney Tunes' point of view./Duck's Reflucks: Baby Daffy has Baby Bugs right where he wants him, as the subject of his digital photography and at the mercy of his endless, egocentric creative whims.

title: The Prince and the Sing-Songy Stag
description: When Prince Ivandoe valiantly sets free Brian the Bard, he discovers he is now stuck with him... until such time that Brian saves Prince Ivandoe's life in return. This would not be so awful if Brian didn't send all day singing accurate, yet deeply unflattering, songs about Prince Ivandoe's looks and abilities.
originalseriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe

title: Ice to Beat You
description: A chilling challenge inside an iceberg leads to the coldest elimination of the season.

title: Bridge Out
description: After an overpass collapses on the highway, Team Tennyson is in a traffic jam along with Simon Sez and family. But when Ben and Simon team up to tackle the gridlock together, Simon only makes matters much, much worse.

title: Lost and Found
description: When Thomas helps Nia make a delivery to the beach in Norramby, he insists he knows a shortcut and leads the way! But it turns out his memory isn't as good as he… remembered.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Chapter 1: The Legs
description: Susie must rely on Oscar and Hedgehog in unimaginable ways after a magic trick gone wrong.

title: Mordecai and the Rigbys
description: After lying about having an awesome band, Mordecai and Rigby must get help from their future selves in order to learn how to play in time for the battle of the bands.

title: The Boredom
description: Gumball and Darwin are convinced it's one of those days when nothing interesting is happening. But as they walk around Elmore in search of adventure, it becomes apparent exciting things are happening just not to them.

title: The Soundhouse
description: Oscar and Hedgehog discover a new structure on the island and become friends with its caretaker.

title: Power Flower/Baby Horsefly/Margo Mayfly
description: Declan makes the rules, visits the horsefly stables, and the bugs welcome a visitor.

title: Moonstruck
description: Grandpa Max reveals the story of how he met Verdona and how he eventually was recruited to become a Plumber.

title: Perfect Day
description: Ben thinks he's having 'the perfect day' only to realize he's been put in a dream world by Enoch and the Forever Knights who are after the Omnitrix. Ben's "dream world" soon becomes a nightmare world, with Ben forced to live out his ultimate terror...being stuck at school! But with Max and Gwen's help, he's able to vanquish his nightmare foes and re-enter the real world where he takes down  Enoch...only to reveal an even more powerful knight...The Forever King.

title: Reflected Glory
description: JT and Cash get in over their heads when they take credit for Ben's heroic acts.

title: More Cowbell
description: Thomas is elated when he finds a cowbell on the side of the tracks, until his friends start hogging it.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Sheep Shenanigans
description: When passing through the snowy pastures of Sodor, Thomas, Percy, and Diesel find an adorable sheep all by herself. When the sheep takes a liking to Diesel, the three engines decide to let her sleep with them in the sheds until they can find out where she came from. However, when the sheep's fluffy herd arrives for an extended sheep-over, the engines realize that their fleecy and noisy guests have overstayed their welcome. Will they be able to get the sheep back home where they came from, or will the baaa-ing sheep continue to disrupt the engines' sleep?
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Ben 10,010
description: In a future where an adult Gwen Tennyson is president and the world is being taken over by the alien horde known as the Xerge, a disillusioned Ben 10000 is called out of retirement to recruit his 10-year old version from the past - only together can the battle-worn adult and the impulsive child save a future under siege.

title: The Secret of Dos Santos
description: Ben and Rook join Kai Green on a perilous alien relic hunt through South America.

title: Cyber Slammers
description: At Biggie Box Japan, Ben waits in an epic line for the release of the latest Sumo Slammers video game, Cyber Slammers, but Ben must save the store not from game-hungry customers, but from Steam Smythe, who wants to retro-fit a massive mech with steam punk powers!

title: Speedster Sandy
description: After yet another victorious race, Kana seems unbeatable! No engine on the island is as fast as Kana! However, this does not stop Sandy from challenging the electric engine. Everyone is sure Kana will win again. Sandy picks the route for the race, using her smarts and her small stature to her advantage! By focusing on her own strengths rather than comparing to Kana's strengths, she makes a fast track to victory!
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: When's My Turn?/A Twig's Tale/Play With Me!
description: The bugs learn to take turns, Lu meets Barnaby's favorite twig, and Lu gets distracted by Biba's baby brother!

title: End of an Era
description: The Time War races towards its dramatic conclusion, with the fate of the entire universe and everything in it since the very beginning of time resting in the hands of the Ben 10.

title: Takers Keepers/D-A-F-F-Y (song)/To Tell the Tooth
description: Takers Keepers: Daffy steals Taz's favorite toy but he learns you can't just take everything you want./To Tell the Tooth: When Bugs loses a baby tooth, Daffy tries to figure out how to scam the tooth fairy.

title: Nor Iron Bars a Cage
description: To settle an old score, Kevin voluntarily returns to the Null Void prison he once escaped.

title: Chapter 13: Jar Guard
description: Mildred's Friend tells a cautionary tale.

title: Truffle Season
description: It's Truffle Season, Apple and Onion are Truffle Hunters and they will stop at nothing to taste a truffle.

title: Universe vs. Tennyson
description: Ben gets dragged into intergalactic court by the other Celestialsapiens (Alien Xs) for recreating the universe (back in "So Long and Thanks for All the Smoothies").

title: Falls, Falls, Falls
description: Team Tennyson looks to take in the sights of the Shoshone Falls, but when they arrive to find Steam Smythe siphoning off the water, it is up to Ben to distract the steam punk baddie long enough to allow Grandpa Max and Gwen the time to shut down the hydropower plant and save the Falls.

title: Tortilla Towel
description: After making Oscar's tortilla towel dreams come true, he and Hedgehog find that running a business is harder than they thought.

title: Tyrannosaurus Wrecks
description: Thomas and the other Engines get to deliver some newly discovered dinosaur bones, but they must deliver them in the correct order for assembly, which isn't as easy as it sounds...
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: My Frabulous Family/Paw Pixie
description: When Apple feels like the loneliest only child, she searches for the perfect sibling amongst her friends. When Stellar loses her first claw and worries it won't grow back, Apple invents a "Paw Pixie" to comfort her.

title: I Got a New Aptitude
description: Buster, Plucky, and Hamton take an aptiTOON test that yields some surprising career prospects. Meanwhile, Babs and Sweetie's relaxing dorm-cation is interrupted by a mysterious smell, and they can't rest until they find the source.

title: I Heart Heartforde
description: Oscar, hedgehog and the other campers are excited to take a trip to the non-magical town of Heartforde.

title: Campers Above the Bed
description: Hedgehog finds a city underneath her bed as she looks for her missing diary.

title: The Secret Serum
description: There's a vampire loose in the town terrorizing the residents and stealing an odd assortment of loot. When the gang does some sniffing around, they discover an unlikely suspect - Daphne's mother. Things are already strained within Mystery Inc. and with this latest blow, the gang is truly torn in half. Girls on one side, boys on the other. Although they solve the mystery in the end, the rift in Mystery Inc. is now complete. They are a team no more.

title: Showdown Part 2
description: Ben must deal with a past failure while a deranged Malware launches his final attack on Azmuth.

title: Ghost Town
description: Vilgax visits Ghostfreak in prison and gets more than he bargained for when Ghostfreak begins possessing the citizens of Vilgaxia.

title: For Whom the Toll Calls/John Jacob Jongle Elmer Fudd (song)/Cereal Boxing
description: For Whom the Toll Calls: Petunia and Tweety learn how to call long distance and amass a huge phone bill./Cereal Boxing: The kids become obsessed with getting the prizes from boxes of sugary cereal.

title: Good Job
description: Falafel is starting to feel very underappreciated as the building's handyman. What's the point in all this back breaking work if not a single person will ever tell him, "Good Job"?

title: King Koil
description: Ben and Gwen spend the day volunteering at Repto Ranch and come face to face with King Koil, but need to quickly overcome their fear of snakes if they are to rescue the released critters and defeat the slithery baddie.

title: And Then There Were None
description: Vilgax and Eon team up to wipe out every Ben in every dimension!

title: Bounty Ball
description: While Gwen listens to a lecture on the Transcontinental Railroad, Ben sneaks away to the gift shop. But once the Bounty Hunters appear and corner our hero, Gwen must relay the information she learned on the train and use it to their advantage to help Ben escape.

title: Jeremiah
description: Oscar finds and cares for a magical root from Susie's yard.

title: Beach Heads
description: After traveling to Tampa Beach, Florida, Team Tennyson hopes to get some much-needed rest & relaxation, but the tempests without a temper, the Weatherheads, have other plans that Ben must thwart: to build a new beach base!

title: Dude Where's Macaw
description: While trying to defend his elite gamer status Chef uses an old cheat code that brings a dangerous avatar to life.

title: Xingo's Back
description: Left to entertain himself as Max takes a much deserved nap, Ben stumbles upon a Xingo arcade game and goes OE-Shock Rock to power it up, but when it receives too much juice, Xingo leaps out into the real world and our hero must go toe-to-toe with his favorite cartoon character.

title: The Unicorns Have Got to Go
description: In order to impress Margret and ask her out, Mordecai hangs with a bunch of punk Unicorns who say they can help him get his lady.

title: Night of the Living Nightmare
description: Albedo is desperate to get his hands on the Ultimatrix and he goes to extreme measures to get it. Once he has invaded Ben's mind, all bets are off.

title: Benwolf
description: In New Mexico, Max stops to visit an old friend, who's a Navajo Chief. Suddenly, a powerful storm comes out of nowhere. And behind bolts of purple lightning, a Navajo werewolf appears. As Ben battles the werewolf, he appears to be bitten and turns into Benwolf.

title: Something I Ate
description: Ben, Gwen, and Max go on a tour of the impervious Fort Knox, but when Dr. Animo sicks a hungry ani-mutate on the Fort, Ben must stop it before it gobbles up the nation's monitory standard!

title: Return to Forever
description: The Forever Knights threaten to use a sinister weapon to erase all alien DNA on Earth unless Ben and Rook can stop them.

title: The Forge of Creation
description: Professor Paradox holds the key to stopping Aggregor from tapping into the limitless power of Alien X.

title: Good as New
description: While out on a delivery to Whiff's Recycling Plant with his beloved buddy Boxy in tow, Thomas realizes that his pal is on his last crooked axle. Inspired by Whiff's talent in turning junk into useful inventions, Thomas recruits Percy to help him on a scrap scavenger hunt so they can make Boxy as good as new! However, mending the broken boxcar proves to be harder than Thomas thought, but with guidance from Whiff and his "secret formula," Thomas and friends reduce, reuse, recycle, and rethink to transform Boxy into a rolling repurposed wonder!
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Many Happy Returns
description: Gwen and Kevin pay Ben a surprise visit, but does Kevin's strange behavior have anything to do with an angry Tetramand princess, or her father's fleet of warships prepared to attack the Earth?

title: The Ultimate Heist
description: Albedo seeks a device that will finally change him back into his Galvan form; meanwhile, Ben is locked in Plumber HQ prison.

title: Drone Shoes
description: Can there exist such a thing as drone shoes? It sounds like they would need a huge power capacity.

title: A Very Percy Valentine's Day
description: It's Valentine's Day and no one on Sodor is happier than Percy -- he gets to deliver everyone's gifts to their friends throughout the island! Unfortunately, his energetic eagerness turns to panic when an accident on the rails causes everyone's presents to fall in the mud! With Thomas' help, Percy discovers a way to still deliver the feelings behind everyone's presents -- by using the gift of song!
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: It's Story Time
description: After the Rustbucket breaks down, Ben, Gwen and Grandpa Max find themselves killing time at the local town library but soon scramble to out maneuver Hex as he searches for a hidden ancient artifact.

title: One Hit Wonder
description: Apple & Onion can't bear to work another day in their dead end jobs at the dollar store but as always, money is the issue. If only there was a way they didn't have to worry about money any more.

title: Cirque-Us
description: After saving a State University Alumni ribbon cutting ceremony, Ben becomes the guest of honor at the upcoming Gala, but when the cirque entertainment turns out be Zombozo, in disguise, Ben must not only defeat the evil clown but his mysterious new sidekick, Pirouette!

title: Gwen 10
description: Gwen gets her hands on the Omnitrix and all its powers and now Ben has to take a backseat as Gwen 10 battles Vilgax for control of the device.

title: Dungeon Doug
description: On a trip into the world of Dungeon Doug, Oscar and his dad find themselves on a father-son bonding mission.

title: Capture the Flag
description: When Percy loses Nia's parade flag before the big parade, Thomas helps them search for it before the event begins.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: A Wide Delivery
description: When the trains must deliver in pairs, Thomas is disappointed to be paired with Diesel instead of his BFF Percy.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Tough Luck
description: Gwen's Lucky Girl powers return when she buys a magical stone at a magic convention in Las Vegas. However, Hex is after the same stone, and after his niece breaks him out of prison, the two set off to retrieve the stone.

title: Ice Cream Headache
description: The campers get magical powers from the witches supply of magic ice cream.

title: Something Zombozo This Way Comes
description: Ben and Rook must stop Zombozo and the Circus Freaks from turning everyone in Bellwood into zombie clowns!

title: Barney's Birthday
description: The kids are making a quilt for Barney's birthday featuring their favorite things to do with Barney. David has a hard time choosing just one thing, so Baby Bop and Billy help him decide just in time for the party.

title: Lil Noodle
description: Apple and Onion must remain legit enough to be in their favorite rapper's music video.

title: Rook Tales
description: Rook's former teacher will preserve Revonnahgander traditions at any cost.

title: Never Say Try/Taz's Fridge (song)/Pair O' Dice Lost
description: Never Say Try: Sylvester is a bad dancer and finger painter so he believes he'll never be good at anything./Pair O' Dice Lost: Daffy feels defeated whenever things aren't going his way.

title: Chicken Nuggets of Wisdom
description: When Ben and Max get into an argument, Ben goes Heatblast to blow off steam against Max's wishes; but once Dr. Animo spots him and subsequently turns Max into a chicken, it's up to Ben to right his wrong if he is to save his Grandpa and stop Dr. Animo.

title: Winter Forecast
description: Steven has to get Connie home before it snows.

title: Trade-Off!
description: Darkstar, convinces Kevin to join him in a quest for an ancient artifact with the ability to help them both escape their current degenerate states.

title: Lights! Camera! Tweety!/Backstage Bugs
description: Lights, Camera, Tweety!: The Baby Looney Tunes are very eager to visit the local TV station, home of their favorite live children's show. When Floyd accidentally locks them inside the studio moments before airtime, they are forced to put on today's program all by themselves!/Backstage Bugs: Baby Bugs can't wait to see his favorite children's musical group, The Wormies, and he absolutely thrills to the notion of possibly meeting his personal hero, Willie Wormie, backstage after the show. But Bugs fails to heed Floyd's warning about staying with the group in the crowded arena and suffers consequences when he gets separated from Floyd.

title: Brand New Track
description: Thomas and Percy explore a brand-new track the evening before the route is opened. Everything seems new and exciting, and even a night spent stuck in the mud turns into a wonderful experience. Only in the light of day do they realize that nothing they saw was really "new" at all - it just seemed so because they brought to it a sense of delight and discovery.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: The Prince and the Playdate
description: Prince Ivandoe is a prisoner in the castle dungeon of Jezabel's mother, Grizabella - the unpredictable and slightly terrifying "Queen of Thieves". Whilst waiting for a royal random, Grizabella encourages her daughter to enjoy her "playdate" with the little prince. Prince Ivandoe is all too eager to do the same. However, when Grizabella demands that Prince Ivandoe perform as her Royal Jester - Ivandoe and Bert realise they need to escape. At once!!
originalseriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe

title: Christmas Mountain
description: It's Christmas time in Sodor and every engine is excitedly preparing for the holiday, especially Bruno who is excited to put his star on the tree. It's his tradition! When the Christmas tree can't be delivered, Thomas and Percy learn why traditions are important to Bruno. They get creative to keep a disappointed Bruno's holiday spirit bright, ultimately transforming Lookout Mountain into the best -- and biggest -- replacement "tree!" Thomas, Percy, and Bruno are joined by their friends to decorate, sing, and celebrate the tradition together!
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Malefactor
description: Khyber and his dog attacks Ben and Rook while they're at the "Olde Bellwood Days" festival, but does the hunter have other plans? (Introducing new Nemetrix alien Hypnotick.)

title: Speechless on the Seine
description: While in Paris, France, Ben catches Zombozo robbing the Louvre, but when Zombozo hypnotizes Ben to remain speechless, Ben must navigate a foreign land like a mime in order to stop the criminal clown and his travelling circus.

title: Crime Alert
description: Robin is ready to answer a crime alert but the other Titans are in no rush.

title: Oddjobs
description: Hedgehog and Oscar investigate problems at U.M.P.S. and meet the new intern, Oddjobs, who's a great friend but a terrible employee.

title: Tummy Trouble
description: When the Incursean armada kidnaps the Gourmand Queen, Ben and Rook must get the warring Gormand factions to work together to save her and stop the Incursean invasion.

title: Andreas' Fault
description: The team discovers that alien con-man Argit has somehow become the leader of the Forever Knights.

title: Big Tick
description: A giant alien tick that sucks planets dry, lands on Earth with the sole purpose of destroying the planet and only a new alien hero can stop it.

title: Outer Space
description: The Looney Builders build Marvin the Martian and his Martian crew a space station. Marvin soon becomes overwhelmed by his Martian crew's antics and lack of personal space.

title: Kevin 11
description: After a big argument with Max, Ben rebels by going out on his own in the Big Apple and makes friends with Kevin 11, who has plans for the Omnitrix.

title: Space Station Scooby!
description: When Neil deGrasse Tyson gets trapped on the International Space Station with a horrible monster, Bill Nye arrives to save his good friend with the help of Velma and our mystery solving gang. Arriving at the space station in the nick of time, our heroes work with these two scientific minds to separate the science from the science fiction when a Tardigrade monster wreaks havoc on the ship.

title: A New Life
description: Apple and Onion both leave their homes and follow their dreams to the big city but things don't go quite to plan.

title: Birth Day Tales/Meer-kitties
description: As everyone waits for the birth of Stripes' meerkat babies, the kids recount stories of their own first birthdays. When Apple's Dads insist on giving Stripes' meerkat pups to other homes, Apple hides them in her room.

title: Iyanu: The Age of Wonders
description: In a prequel set 500 years before The Chosen's arrival, Yorubaland thrives in the Age of Wonders. When Meje, the embodiment of the seven deadly sins, emerges, warriors Dara and Ishe must prevent the Age of Darkness with help from the Divine Ones.

title: The Music Store Thief
description: Instruments have been going missing from Apple and Onion's favourite music store and Chicken Nugget (who's in charge of security) doesn't want them hanging around and getting in the way.

title: Digital Quality
description: Ben and Gwen don't want to go to the CD Library. CDs are for old people. Ew. Once Team Tennyson is there, Lord Decibel traps them inside and demands a ransom. Ben and Gwen find Kevin inside on a potentially nefarious quest of his own, but it turns out that Lord Decibel may have already found the item that they so desperately desire.

title: Funhouse
description: The Tennysons find themselves stuck inside an inescapable funhouse constructed by Zombozo; Ben goes alien and fights for escape, ultimately proving that behind every illusion, there's a disappointing secret.

title: The Visitor
description: A mysterious alien named Xylene shows up and wants to return the Omnitrix to its rightful owner, Grandpa Max!

title: Super Alien Hero Buddy Adventures
description: Ben discovers his alien heroes have been ripped off by a lame cartoon and he is not happy. So he sets out to make things right.

title: Rigby's Body
description: After Rigby eats an excessive amount of junk food, his body quits on him, leaving him a ghost-like consciousness. Mordecai and Skips must find his body before the day is over.

title: Creature Feature
description: When Max dozes off before a double feature, Ben and Gwen are left to save the drive-in by themselves as the evil magician Hex brings the movie monster "That" to life, and unleashes him on the unsuspecting moviegoers.

title: Tourist Trap
description: While messing with the World's Largest Rubberband Ball at a tourist trap, Ben accidently releases some mischievous electrical creatures.

title: Side Effects
description: Ben catches a cold and the symptoms wreak havoc on his alien heroes. To make matters even worse, he has to battle a creature made from cockroaches.

title: Revenge of the Man Crab
description: While hosting a volleyball tournament for Trickell's Triquid diet moisture, a smooth drinking beverage just like water except not so fatty, Crystal Cove beach finds itself attacked by a hideous man crab, who has taken a liking to the tournament's female players. Desperate to stop this beast before it scares away all the tourists, the gang investigates convinced it is a disgruntled local named Skipper Shelton, famous for his delicious clam filled waffle cones, his missing nose and his hatred for Crystal Cove bureaucrats. But when Daphne is captured by the Man Crab, Scooby and the gang have to put the mystery solving into overdrive or risk losing not only Daphne but the sanity of their leader Fred, who is not taking the abduction well.

title: Apple's Focus
description: Apple decides to help Onion achieve his dream of competing on a baking show.

title: Susie and her Sister Chapter 1: Heathers
description: Susie's new little sister has a gift for magic, but it's causing problems for the community. Will Susie learn to accept that Mildred is more powerful, and will the townsfolk be able to accept the most powerful witch in the world?

title: Cool for Cats/Ten Loonies in a Bed (song)/Time Out!
description: Cool for Cats: Sylvester believes a commercial that says eating Chewy Chomps will make him cool./Time Out!: Bugs, Daffy and Taz are disciplined by having a time out in the corner.

title: Election Day
description: Apple and Onion realize that the Mayor of their city is corrupt and they vow to put an end to that.

title: Who's Your Granny?/If You're Looney (song)/The Tattletale
description: Who's Your Granny?: When Granny gets sick, Lola tries to take over her responsibilities./The Tattletale: Lola begins tattling on the other babies until her friends no longer want to play with her.

title: Mom's Sandwich/ Picnic Hill/ Sit Still Sonia
description: Sonia, Hugo and Mel have Sunday adventures making a sandwich for Mom, finding a picnic spot, and learning the benefits of taking a break.

title: The Ballad of Mr. Baumann
description: The grouchy storekeeper has a big secret, and she's not of this Earth.

title: Chapter 20: It Takes Time
description: The island welcomes a new era.

title: Creature Mysteries
description: Ranger Tabes tells the Bears she's been investigating a mysterious creature. But when the Bears realize she's actually investigating their friend Charlie, they split up to ensure Charlie's safety.

title: Ben 10 vs. Negative 10 Part 1
description: Ben, Max Ben and Gwen investigate a couple of daring break-ins, only to discover they were both once secret Plumber installations. What our heroes find out is that those responsible for the break-ins are working for The Forever King. He's brought together a rogue's gallery of some of Ben's most notorious enemies to eventually steal the world's most powerful energy source...located deep inside the Plumber bunker at Mount Rushmore.

title: The Final Battle Part 2
description: A defeated Ben gives up the Omnitrix to save himself and his friends. Powerless, he boards Vilgax's ship for their final battle!

title: Sameroo
description: Gordon has a day-long assignment for Thomas and the Troublesome Trucks -- they have to transport delivery after delivery to Vicarstown! The Troublesome Trucks are less than enthused -- this "sameroo" job will bore them out of their bolts! The Number One Engine is determined to make the day "amazeroo" for them and does his best to turn their repeated route into a new adventure! After their game of "Switcheroo" gets them lost, Thomas and the Troublesome Trucks learn that routine is not necessarily a bad thing -- in fact, it can be very helpful!
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: The Babies Chapter 1: Breakfast Errands
description: Frustrated that he doesn't know his magical identity, Oliver convinces Susie to tell him by means of nonviolent protest. Not wanting anyone in her house, Susie takes Oliver on a series of errands to help him figure it out.

title: Pinecone Palooza/The Big Footed Cave Bird
description: Grandma and Timmy are entering the Pinecone Art Show by carving a sculpture out of stone… that is, if they can learn how to carve./Ranger Nat is hiking and comes across the Big-Footed Cave Bird, and realizes it can't get back into her home.

title: Deep
description: Ben, Kevin, and Gwen journey to the center of an all-water planet in an attempt to finally of capture Aggregor.

title: The Trade
description: After accidentally trading away Chad's favorite baseball card, Clarence has to trade it back! Determined to become an expert, Clarence transforms himself into a slick salesman, before facing the ultimate deal.

title: A Nightmare on Aberdale Street: Balance's Revenge
description: In this Halloween adventure, Clarence uses a special jack-o-lantern to enter the world of people's dreams. He discovers that something mysterious is causing his friends to have nightmares, and Clarence needs to stop it!

title: Make a Wish/ Forever Castle/ Stringy Soup
description: Sonia, Hugo and Mel have Sunday adventures making wishes, sand castles, and speaking their mind while being kind.

title: The Tunnel
description: After Clarence accidentally knocks Belson's new video game down a storm drain, Belson enters the large underground sewer tunnel to retrieve it. When Belson doesn't return, Clarence must decide whether or not to go in after him.

title: A Matter of Pride
description: Apple & Onion's jobs have become too demeaning. They decide to put their foots down. It's a matter of pride.

title: The Perfect Team
description: Onion worries his relationship with Apple is in jeopardy when a stray cat enters the picture.

title: Mock 10
description: Ben, Kevin and La Grange find themselves stuck 'outside of time' after the latter hijacks a supersonic train with a faulty engine, forcing the trio to team up and slow down.

title: Broccoli
description: Some major construction is taking place on the roof of Apple and Onion's building and they can't get back home till it's finished.

title: Falafel's Car Keys
description: Apple & Onion are deemed responsible enough to borrow Falafel's car for their first road trip together. Nothing will go wrong, and they're going to make sure of that… by getting some practice in.

title: Girl Trouble
description: Gwen's cousin, Sunny, pays a visit but she's more than meets the eye!

title: Innervasion
description: The mysteries of the Omni-Enhancements are solved when Ben battles an alien invasion coming from inside the Omnitrix.

title: The Last Cookie/ Crab's Home/ Magic Trick
description: Sonia, Hugo and Mel have Sunday adventures solving a cookie mystery, building a home for a crab, and learning to think on their feet.

title: Baba Yaga House
description: Squatter Otter tries to win Panda's trust and convince the Bears to live in a mysterious house.

title: High Stress Express
description: During a live feed of the new transcontinental bullet train, La Grange enters the picture to outrace the train, but Ben joins in on the fun and will stop at nothing to come out on top!

title: Susie's Fantastical Scavenger Hunt
description: Oscar and Hedgehog must learn to exist without each other when they are put on different teams during a scavenger hunt.

title: Oversimulated Much
description: Clover feels that Zerlina doesn't take her seriously as a spy and is determined to prove herself at WOOHP Training Day. But when the simulations go wrong and agents blank out, the Spies realize a secret mastermind is causing the chaos.

title: Hero Time
description: A starstruck Ben dates a beautiful young movie actress, while his childhood hero makes a comeback.

title: He's Just Not Here Right Now
description: Oscar and Hedgehog encounter New Jersey's most famous piece of folklore.

title: Saxophone Come Home
description: Oscar befriends a teenage Yeti.

title: Log Cabin Fever/A Mid-Autumn Night's Scream
description: Log Cabin Fever: Granny takes the Baby Looney Tunes back to a simpler lifestyle during a rustic weekend spent in an 1800's log cabin, where they learn to enjoy life minus all modern conveniences. Baby Bugs and Baby Daffy get in trouble for smuggling their palm-sized computer game along, and they face Granny's consequences./A Mid-Autumn Night's Scream: The Baby Looney Tunes first Halloween involves a costume contest for Lola, Melissa and Petunia, group trick-or-treating and Sylvester overcoming his fear of confronting an allegedly scary neighbor.

title: Dragon Run
description: Thomas has the honor of pulling the dragon to the Medieval Faire, but everyone wants a turn as well.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: The Most Dangerous Game Show
description: Ben fights for his life on an alien reality show.

title: Bros in Space
description: Rook brings Ben to his home planet to meet the family. Unbeknownst to them, an old foe is raising an army to steal the planet's most precious resource!  (Introducing Rook's family.)

title: Bon Voyage
description: Aboard the SS Pettigrew on its final voyage, Ben must not only battle seasickness but Steam Smythe, who looks to use his mechanical creatures to sink the steamship's modern replacement and the passengers with it!

title: X Equals Ben Plus 2
description: The Incursians blame Earth for the kidnapping of Emperor Milleus' daughter, Attea. Raff, the Emperor's right-hand man, recruits Kevin to help them recover Attea before the Emperor uses the Conquest Ray to destroy the Earth. Ben transforms into Alien X but soon discovers his powers are too great to control. Ben must gain control over Alien X before Emperor Milleus can use the Conquest Ray to blow up Earth.

title: Hunted
description: Three alien bounty hunters are hot on Ben's trail. But one of them is a secret agent trying to make sure the Omnitrix does not fall into evil hands.

title: Be-Knighted
description: The Forever Knights have secured an alien weapon that will help them kill a dragon they have held captive for centuries. After the dragon escapes, they must ask Ben for help in recapturing it. Ben agrees to help but soon discovers the real identity of the dragon along with its ulterior motive for wanting to return to the Forever Knights. Ben must use his head, not just his brawn, in finding a peaceful solution to the impending fight between the dragon and the knights.

title: A Quiet Delivery
description: Thomas volunteers to get a sleeping Annie and Clarabel across Sodor without waking them up, only to discover that it's going to be harder than he imagined.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Fool's Gold
description: When an alien named Orb asks for help finding his missing friend, Decka, Ben, Gwen and Kevin are surprised to learn just how valuable a friend he is.

title: Let Them Eat Quack
description: Plucky is named ruler of a kingdom, and the toons visit his castle as he ascends the throne. Before long, Plucky exerts power over his friends, Sweetie tries to overthrow the monarchy, and Hamton lives out his fantasy of the landed gentry.

title: Sweet Tooth
description: While on a trip to the dentist's office, a paranoid Ben grows uneasy over the dentist's odd behavior and goes into hiding, but when his suspicions prove right, and the dentist transforms into the monstrous Toothache, Ben must pull himself together if he is to save the day!

title: Run, Mama, Run!/Rainbow Rhino BURP Tomato
description: Apple and Stellar help Mama Crocker attend both Josh's diving and Jamie's ballet performance. Apple and her friends form a pop band to cheer up grumpy Papa. But will their song warm his heart, or hurt his ears?

title: Absolute Power Part 2
description: It's Ben and company's last stand against a foe they can't bring themselves to fight!

title: Mani - Pedi
description: After defeating Brother Blood, the Titans reward themselves with a trip to the nail salon.

title: Don't Laze Me, Bro
description: Ben and his arch-enemy Billy Billions clash in a duel for supremacy at the world's largest Laser Tag Park, LASER TOWN. But, when Billy inadvertently ignites a robot rebellion, and the lasers are set from tag to disintegrate, their childish game escalates into a full blown war! The two foes find that they must set aside their petty differences and team up in order to make it out alive, let alone save the day!

title: This One Goes to 11
description: During one last stop by a toy store before Ben, Gwen, and Grandpa Max's maiden voyage across the Atlantic, Ben runs into an old bully, Kevin 11, who now has new powers. He's able to transform into aliens just like Ben, such as the bootleg doppelganger of Cannonbolt. Wreckingbolt!

title: Bomzobo Lives
description: During a routine trip to the DMV, Max takes a driving test to renew his license, but when a disguised Zombozo hijacks the role of instructor, Ben goes alien to stop the baddie and save their family road trip.

title: The Prince and the Princenappers
description: Whilst travelling through the notoriously dangerous Forest of Outlaws, Prince Ivandoe is repeatedly Princenapped! First by a gang of wolves in disguise, then by Boaris and his Merry Boars, and finally by Feral and her gang of cat-thieves - all of them hoping to secure a royal ransom. Luckily for Prince Ivandoe and Bert, they are rescued by the fair Jezabel - though, as it turns out, not with the noblest of intentions.
originalseriesname: The Heroic Quest of the Valiant Prince Ivandoe

title: Islands Part 7: Helpers
description: Finn and his friends journey to a last refuge called Founders Island.

title: The Real Number One
description: When Thomas' #1 is covered by paint, he sets out to prove to himself that he is still number one, but when everything starts to go wrong for him, he learns what it really means to be #1.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Ready to Rumble
description: After Ben thinks he's broken Gwen's computer, he sneaks off and enters an "ultimate wrestling competition" to win enough money to buy her a new one. On the mat as Fourarms, he becomes an instant celebrity hit with the fans and ends up going up against a tandem of odd looking brothers with special mutant-like powers. Initially adversaries, Ben and the brothers become allies when Ben discovers the brothers are beholden to a powerful mob boss. Ben helps the brothers defeat the mob boss and his henchmen, and in the end realizes Gwen's computer was never really broken.

title: Charmed, I'm Sure
description: Still stranded on the monster planet Anur Transyl, Ben and Rook reluctantly team up with Charmcaster to take on Zs' Skayr.

title: The Gauntlet
description: After years of Ben being picked on by the school bullies Cash and JT, Ben stands up for himself and embarrasses both of them in front of a group of peers. An upset Cash later retaliates by pushing Kevin's GTO down a hill where a robot hand pops out of the trunk after it hits a tree. Cash and JT steal off with the glove only to have the glove possess Cash, granting him the power to get revenge on Ben.

title: Gotcha/Sing Along/Big Laugh
description: The bugs play hide and seek, sing a song, and laugh together.

title: Revenge of the Swarm
description: When Julie is kidnapped, Ben blames Elena who swears she had nothing to do with it. But the nanochips in her lab point to the truth.

title: The Alliance
description: As Fourarms, Ben works to thwart an armored truck robbery by a tough female gang leader named Joey, who delivers a disturbing message from Vilgax.

title: Barb and the Spotted Bears Chapter 3: Nightcap
description: Barb and the elves band together to protect the source of all magic from a pair of fiendish intruders. But will Barb be able to outsmart two rascals as old as the world itself?

title: I Don't Like You
description: Ben and Gwen's social media battle with Kevin 11 quickly escalates into an all-out war in real life.

title: Greetings from Techadon
description: A mysterious object crashes in the center of Bellwood, unleashing Techadon robots with one thing on their mind, destroying Ben!

title: Shake, Rattle, & Bruno
description: When Bruno comes along to help Diesel get a heavy load to the Lighthouse, Bruno tries suggesting a safer route, but Diesel doesn't wait long enough to listen to him. When Diesel barrels though Crumble Canyon, Bruno must brake hard to keep them safe. The squeal causes a rock avalanche and blocks them in. Diesel learns to open his ears to collaborate with Bruno on a solution that uses both their strengths to get out.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Christmas Spirit
description: Apple & Onion know exactly what gifts they want this Christmas but all their money has been squandered. Luckily they find a suitably festive way to make back that money.

title: Cough It Up
description: Psyphon and a gang of bounty hunters are after Argit, who is in possession of a dangerous weapon!

title: If It's Broke, Fix It
description: Dibble helps Grumpy work on his latest invention, a device to stop Bluster's bad vibe plow. Dibble's endless high spirits and sense of fun wear on Grumpy, until he finally says she can't work with him anymore. It's only later that Grumpy understands he needs Dibble's free-spirit inventiveness and creative energy.

title: Kana Recharges
description: Tired and in need of relaxation, Kana decides to take a well-deserved break between deliveries. When she tells Thomas that she wants time all by herself, Thomas is worried that he and the other engines have done something to upset her. Determined to right their assumed wrongs, Thomas and friends follow Kana around the island to convince her to play with them -- the exact opposite of what she needs! When a big storm reaches Sodor, Kana teaches her friends about the value of spending time alone and "feeling the hush."
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Weapon XI Part 1
description: Kevin and Argit attempt to warn the amalgam kids about the Rooters intentions meanwhile Ben, Rook, and Gwen set off to find Kevin and land themselves in the Null Void!

title: More Than a Pretty Engine
description: After a fierce storm causes a rockslide in Crumble Canyon, mountain engine Ashima is eager to clean and clear the chaos with her new friends. However, Thomas and the others are concerned: if Ashima were to help them, the mucky mess could ruin her beautiful paint! When the friends' fussiness prevents Ashima from working with the team, she has to prove to Thomas and the others that they shouldn't judge her by her appearance.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Couples Retreat
description: After Darkstar opens the Door to Anywhere, Charmcaster comes through and the two team up to give Ben, Gwen and Kevin the fight of a lifetime.

title: Rad
description: With Plumber agents trapped in Incursean territory, Ben and Rook must employ the services of Rad Dudesman, the roughest, toughest smuggler in the galaxy.  (Introducing Rad Dudesman, return of classic Ben alien, Eye Guy.)

title: Max to the Max
description: While Ben, Gwen, and Max hike to a waterfall, the Bugg Brothers are back with a plan to duplicate Diamondhead; but when their cloning ray gun fires on Max instead, multiplying him endlessly, Gwen and Ben must round up all the Maxes while also fighting off the Bugg Brothers.

title: All Washed Up/My Bunny Lies Over the Ocean (song)/Did Not! Did Too!
description: All Washed Up: Taz decides he doesn't like taking a bath./Did Not! Did Too!: Bugs and Lola temporarily decide that they don't want to be friends any longer.

title: Daddy Date Night/Croc Swap
description: Apple is anxious about her Dads leaving her with a babysitter on their date night. But she has a solution: She'll join them! Annoyed that they're treated the same on their birthday, Josh and Jamie swap places to see if their friends notice.

title: Hair Cut-Ups/Does Your Tongue Hang Low (song)/A Clean Sweep
description: Hair Cut-Ups: Lola is afraid of getting her first haircut./A Clean Sweep: Daffy tries to avoid cleaning up by sweeping his toys under a rug.

title: Mystery, Incorporeal
description: An old enemy emerges while Ben and Rook visit Kevin and Gwen at college.

title: Lucky Girl
description: Ben battles an evil sorcerer whose power whose emanates from mystic charms, one of which turns Gwen into her own superhero named Lucky Girl.

title: The Beginning of the End
description: As the final battle between the Forever Knights and Dagon's Esoterica heats up, Ben finds himself caught in the middle of an intergalactic showdown.

title: Chapter 3: See Bees? Gee! Bees!
description: Oscar heads to the Sasquatch Monastery in search of enlightenment.

title: World Cup
description: It's time to relax in the expensive massage chairs that Apple & Onion have rented for the month. It's also time for the Football (soccer) World Cup and Falafel's team, Egypt are in the tournament..

title: Burger's Trampoline
description: After learning that Burger has a trampoline, Apple and Onion pay him a visit. Burger thinks they came especially to see him and is overjoyed.

title: Chapter 6: Miracle Rabbit
description: Oscar and Ramona run an errand on the moon.

title: Blue Engine Blues
description: After getting through a rough night's sleep and finding out his beach day gets cancelled due to the rain, Thomas winds up in the grumpiest of moods. Encountering Riff and Jiff with their usual happy-go-lucky attitudes, Thomas comes to the conclusion that he'll only be liked when he appears happy. He puts on fake smile for the rest of the day, but his words don't match his demeanor and everyone can see right through him. Finally, Thomas comes across Riff and Jiff again, who reveal they're also upset about the cruddy day! They teach him that nobody can be happy all the time, and sometimes you need a friend to vent to on the days you're most blue.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Evil's Encore
description: Dr. Animo reminisces about when he once took control of the Plumber's HQ in Mount Rushmore. (Flashback episode.)

title: Wind Some, Lose Some
description: At the Mojave Wind Farm in Texas, Max and Gwen plan to set Ben straight on his kooky ideas about how wind works, but when they find the Weatherheads using the towering turbines for their latest nefarious plan, will Ben face facts in time to blow them away?

title: Howl of the Fright Hound
description: After a horrible, mechanized beast begins attacking the town, all fingers begin pointing at Scooby. Before the gang can clear his name, the Sheriff has Scooby hauled away to the Crystal Cove Hospital for Criminally Insane Animals. Now, it's up to the gang to clear Scooby's good name. But standing in their way is a new enemy they hadn't counted on: a diabolical parrot named Professor Pericles, who knows more about Mystery Inc. than he should. Add to this the growing friction between Shaggy, Velma and Scooby, and you have a recipe for disaster.

title: Chapter 12: Night's Pockets
description: Pajamas and Jimjams try to find Time.

title: You Poor Saps
description: Tensions run high in this week's challenge when the Campers find themselves in a sticky situation.

title: Apple's in Charge
description: Apple is put in charge of the Dollar Store for the very first time.

title: Everyone's Tube
description: Through a standard video browsing session online, we get a glimpse of the different kinds of videos the Bears have posted.

title: Cool Guy Clarence
description: When Clarence meets JT, the kid who mows their lawn, he finds a fast friend who shows him some cool new music, a new outlook on life and a sweet rat-tail! Clarence leans into the rat tail lifestyle, discovering a whole new side of Aberdale he never knew existed.

title: Bottomless Ben
description: While visiting Carlsbad Caverns National Park, the Tennyson's come across the "Bottomless Pit", a naturally formed pit with no bottom. Ben fights his better judgment to jump in the pit and be the first person to find the bottom, until Kevin 11 shows up and starts to goad Ben into a contest to the bottom of the pit! The natural rivalry is put on hold, however, with the arrival of Breaker One-Nine, who has come to destroy the Caverns!

title: You Remind Me of Someone
description: Ben and Gwen look for the infamous Bojamboo (the Bigfoot of the South) and discover that it's actually the Forgeti, at the same time as Kevin 11, but when Ben and Kevin are blasted with the Forgeti's forgetfulness mist, they reverse roles and it's up to Gwen and Max to restore them back to normal.

title: Thomas' Day Off
description: When all the trains but Thomas get deliveries, he's left to spend the day alone. With the help of an old boxcar and a battered beachball... an adventure unfolds.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Way Back Wendel
description: Courtney must deliberately lose a challenge or let the entire world go back in time. It's a really hard choice for her.

title: The Monsters in Your Head
description: Ben and Gwen learn a rumor of an alien invasion happening at the park they are camping at, but when they investigate, they discover a preserve containing a host of mutated creatures engineered by Animo! With the unexpected help of Kevin 11 and his family, Ben proves that the rumors are false, and that truth is stranger than fiction!

title: Goodbye Mr. Giggles/The Spoonasaurus
description: When Josh's favourite hyena toy is lost forever, his friends arrange a "toy farewell" for the beloved Mr.Giggles. At Dr. Digby's Dino Park, Stellar and Apple clash over facts until their argument topples a spectacular spinosaurus skeleton!

title: Talent Show
description: Clarence throws a big talent show in his yard to showcase all the fun hidden talents of his friends. But when Brady claims he's talentless, Clarence sets out to prove that everyone has something special to share!

title: The Chupaca-bro
description: Team Tennyson discovers that a small village's goats are being terrorized by the legendary Chupacabra, but when Ben realizes it's actually Dr. Animo, our hero must thwart the dastardly doctor before he uses the essence of the goats to power up into an unstoppable form!

title: Rad Monster Party
description: Ben and Rook enlist the help of intergalactic smuggler Rad Dudesman to fly them through the Anur System, the home of the monstrous aliens!

title: Birds of a Feather
description: When Vivie longs to be just like a beautiful bird in the park, Barney uses games and imaginative play to help her discover ways to enjoy a similar experience of looking, singing, and even flying like a bird!

title: Letting Off Steam
description: When Thomas and Percy get into their first big fight they're afraid that their friendship is over... until Nia helps them figure out how to resolve it.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Mind Your Manners/Down by the Cage (song)/Petunia the Piggy Bank
